title: King's visit to France could be disrupted by protests over retirement age reform
description: The King's first state visit of his reign may be disrupted by ongoing French protests against President Emmanuel Macron's plan to raise the retirement age.

title: Young boys rescued from sewer after crawling into tunnel were told to 'scream as loud as they could'
description: Five boys aged 11 and 12 who became trapped in the New York City sewer system were told to "scream as loud as they could" to help firefighters locate them before being rescued.

title: Gwyneth Paltrow's ski crash caused 'victim' to 'pretty much' lose his love of life
description: Gwyneth Paltrow's accuser "pretty much" lost his love of life after the actress allegedly crashed into the back of him in a skiing hit-and-run, a US court has been told.

title: TikTok 'not an agent of China': Chief executive defends video app during tense US Congress hearing
description: TikTok's chief executive has sought to reassure US Congress that the Chinese-owned video app is not "an agent" of Beijing and poses no risk to national security.

title: Indian MP Rahul Gandhi sentenced to two years in prison for defaming prime minister
description: An Indian opposition leader has been sentenced to two years in prison for making defamatory remarks about Prime Minister Narendra Modi.

title: 'What did they do to deserve this?': Mother's heartbreak at three children killed in besieged Yemen city
description: Two pickup trucks with half a dozen heavily armed men on board escort us on the journey into the besieged city of Taiz.

title: Politician, wife and medical 'middleman' found guilty of organ harvesting plot
description: A Nigerian senator, his wife and a medical "middleman" have been found guilty of conspiring to traffic a market trader to the UK to harvest his kidney.

title: Holocaust survivor becomes TikTok star aged 85
description: A holocaust survivor who hid among dead bodies at the Auschwitz concentration camp has become a TikTok star at the age of 85.

title: More cases of 'highly virulent, Ebola like' Marburg virus found in Equatorial Guinea
description: Equatorial Guinea has confirmed another eight cases of the "highly virulent” Marburg virus.

title: Albanian PM calls out home secretary for 'disgraceful' moment but praises Rishi Sunak
description: The singling out of Albanian migrants in the UK has been a "very, very disgraceful moment in British politics", the country's prime minister has said.

title: Tyson Fury v Oleksandr Usyk undisputed title fight is now off
description: The Tyson Fury versus Oleksandr Usyk fight is now off.

title: France national strike over pension reform: Why are workers so angry?
description: A national strike is taking place in France after President Emmanuel Macron's circumvention of parliament to pass the divisive pension bill which would raise the retirement age by two years.
